    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>In aqueous solution, the hydronium ion ( $\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}+$ ) can get further hydrated to form various hydrated species. Among the options provided, the species that forms is:</p>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{H}_9 \\mathrm{O}_4^{+} $$</p>\n<p>This species, $\\mathrm{H}_9 \\mathrm{O}_4^{+}+$, represents a hydronium ion that is surrounded by three water molecules, forming a more complex hydrated structure often referred to as the \"Eigen cation\".</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mahyy7tb/41dbd6e4-3ded-4949-8b19-20d5144e1cc8/925da9f0-2d79-11f0-81ed-0bc3a40c506b/file-jaoe38c1mahyy7tc.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mahyy7tb/41dbd6e4-3ded-4949-8b19-20d5144e1cc8/925da9f0-2d79-11f0-81ed-0bc3a40c506b/file-jaoe38c1mahyy7tc.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IAT (IISER) 2023 Chemistry - Hydrogen and It's Compounds Question 1 English Explanation\">",
